│ (V->getType()->isFPOrFPVector())\n    return Builder.CreateFNeg(V);\n  return              │
│ Builder.CreateNeg(V); // This is the bug.\n```\n\nThe call `Builder.CreateNeg(V)` creates  │
│ a `neg` instruction (which is canonicalized to `sub 0, V`) without any overflow flags. The │
│ correct behavior is to propagate the `HasNSW` and `HasNUW` flags from the `Negator` object │
│ to this new instruction.\n\n### 4. Proposed Edit Point(s)\n\nThe fix is to modify the      │
│ `CreateNeg` call to pass the stored overflow flags.\n\n**File**:                           │
