│ `nsw`/`nuw` properties as the original operation that was being negated. This prevents the │
│ introduction of new undefined behavior.\n\n### 5. Conclusion\n\nBy propagating the `nsw`   │
│ and `nuw` flags when creating new negation instructions within the `Negator` utility, the  │
│ optimizer will correctly preserve the program's semantics with respect to signed/unsigned  │
